50|$|A {{modified}} Wolter I telescope {{design that}} uses grazing incidence optics to image the <b>solar</b> <b>corona's</b> hottest components (0.5 to 10 Million K) with an angular resolution consistent with 1 arcsec pixels at the CCD. The telescope has an imaging {{field of view}} of 34 arcminutes. It is capable of capturing {{an image of the}} full sun when pointed {{at the center of the}} solar disk. The telescope was designed and built by Smithsonian Astrophysical Observatory (SAO), which, with the Harvard College Observatory (HCO) form the Harvard-Smithsonian Center for Astrophysics (CfA). The camera was developed by NAOJ and JAXA.|$|R
